{"body": "Yes, it looks clearer. But then shouldn't we also apply it for the others for consistency? For example:\r\n\r\n    match ':controller/:action'\r\n    =>  /:controller/:action(.:format) :controller#:action\r\n\r\n    match ':controller(/:action(/:id))', :id => /\\d+/\r\n    =>  /:controller(/:action(/:id))(.:format) :controller#:action {:id=>/\\d+/}\r\n\r\nIn other words, we put `:controller` and `:action` where it's empty.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2468581", "created_at": "2011-10-20T13:30:45Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3337#issuecomment-2468581", "updated_at": "2011-10-20T13:30:45Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3337, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/htanata", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/38becc6fc03453ccb1edfcdea1122408?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff2a40c043c478051e6230e5c6be59d0f.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/received_events", "gravatar_id": "38becc6fc03453ccb1edfcdea1122408", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "htanata", "type": "User", "id": 21238, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/htanata/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383783bd3543c15100fe86"}, "id": 2468581, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3337"}
